OSOGBO  – Artisans and tradesmen as­sociation under the aegis of Ajegunle Tradesmen and Ar­tisans Association have de­clared that they were pleased with the style of governance and performance of Gover­nor Adegboyega Oyetola ad­ministration in Osun State. The tradesmen and arti­sans gave the commendation in Osogbo, Osun State capital, during the inauguration of the newly elected executive of the association held at Nelson Mandela Freedom Park. The traders, who are mainly spare parts and car dealers, acknowledged the achievements of the adminis­tration in the last three years and commended Oyetola for making deliberate efforts to improve the socio-economic fortunes of the state. 2023: I’ll Rather Return Home Than Join APC – Senator… NURTW Clashes: Bode George Blames Sanwo-Olu, Says Lagos Island… While declaring support for the Governor and his second term bid, the Chair­man of the association, Al­haji Azeez Kamarudeen, said Oyetola has done excellently well and as such deserved an­other term in office. Kamarudeen, who noted that the entire Ajegunle’s traders and artisans were resolute to mobilise mas­sively for the governor’s re-election, added that they were pleased with his style of governance and sterling performance. He identified some of the achievements of the Governor as the basis of their support, noting that they had felt the ef­fect of the regular payment of salaries to workers in the state and other good works done by the administration. “Sir, your tenure should not stop at one term, as var­ious organizations, societies and individuals speak high­ly of your accomplishments in the state and urge you to continue the good work, we are all in support of your second term bid, because you deserve it.